McDonnell Douglas saidit signed a technical assistance agreement with the China GreatWall Industries Co for possible use of its Payload AssistModule on the Chinese Long March series of rockets.    The company said the pact will serve as the basis for allfuture proposals involving the use of the Payload Assist Modulein China.    "This agreement opens the door for us to proceed withproposals to the Chinese government or with spacecraftcustomers planning to use the Long March," said Daniel Green,the company's vice president of marketing. Reuter&#3;